  "narrative": {
    "intro": "The NAICS 541990 federal contract market has recorded $6.9B in obligations for FY2026 to date, spread across 5,766 awards with an average award size of $1.2M. Obligations are down 42.0% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Recent fiscal history shows obligations of $10.8B in FY21, $11.7B in FY22, $14.5B in FY23, $14.2B in FY24, and $11.9B in FY25 before the current $6.9B level in FY26. The Department of Defense and the Department of Energy are the largest buyers so far in FY2026, with $2.3B and $1.9B in obligations respectively, followed by the General Services Administration at $1B. Major contractors receiving FY2026 obligations include BATTELLE ENERGY ALLIANCE, LLC at $1.8B, HII MISSION TECHNOLOGIES CORP at $480M, and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC at $421M. This data reflects federal contract obligations to date and does not represent a full fiscal year total.",
